# Testing Standards

## Core Principles

- High-priority requirements must have automated verification.
- Write the failing test before the main implementation.
- Every bug fix must include a regression test.
- Tests must target real risk. Do not write low-value tests just to claim coverage.

## Test Layers

- White-box Unit: verify pure logic, transformations, edge cases, and key branches
- Integration: verify modules, interfaces, and dependency collaboration
- E2E: verify the most critical user or system flows
- Performance: verify performance targets and high-load behavior
- Security: verify auth, authorization, input validation, and sensitive-data protection

## Change Requirements

- When requirements change, check whether `docs/workflow/04-verification/README.md` needs to change too.
- When external contracts change, prioritize integration or end-to-end coverage.
- When a new risky path appears, record it explicitly in the regression strategy.
- For critical paths, explicitly state whether white-box, performance, and security coverage applies; if it applies, implement it, and if not, explain why.
